==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calver
<hw>Cal"ver</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧l"v⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To cut in slices and pickle, as salmon.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For a change, leave <qex>calvered</qex> salmon and eat sprats.</q>
<rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To crimp; <as>as, <ex>calvered</ex>
salmon</as>.</def> <rj><au>Nares.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calver</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Calver
<hw>Cal"ver</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To bear, or be susceptible of,
being calvered; <as>as, grayling's flesh will
<ex>calver</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Catton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calvessnout</ent>⟦br⟧
